methods.businessTime:
Sets this Axis's AxisTransform as an AxisTransformBusinessCalendar.

*Overload 1*  
  :param calendar: (io.deephaven.time.calendar.BusinessCalendar) - business calendar of the AxisTransformBusinessCalendar
  :return: (io.deephaven.plot.AxisImpl) this Axis using the specified business calendar.
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param sds: (io.deephaven.plot.filters.SelectableDataSet) - selectable data set (e.g. OneClick filterable table) containing the business calendar.
  :param calendar: (java.lang.String) - name of a column containing String values, where each value is the name of a
          BusinessCalendar.
  :return: (io.deephaven.plot.AxisImpl) this Axis using the business calendar from row 0 of the filtered sds for the business calendar.
           If no value is found, no transform will be applied.
  
*Overload 3*  
  :return: (io.deephaven.plot.AxisImpl) this Axis using the default business calendar.
  
*Overload 4*  
  :param useBusinessTime: (boolean) - true to use a business time axis transform; false to use a linear axis transform.
  :return: (io.deephaven.plot.AxisImpl) this Axis using the default business calendar or this Axis using a linear axis transform.
